member.name: T:SsoCloud.SsoCloudRequest
member.summary: * For security, this structure is used to make a Cloud SSO login or logout request rather than sending the parameters in the URL or in a form. A typical call is: https://www.keepersecurity.com/api/rest/sso/saml/login/123456789?payload=encodedEncryptedAPIRequestContainingAnSsoCloudRequest

member.name: P:SsoCloud.SsoCloudRequest.Embedded
member.summary: If true, the login/logout result is embedded in a web page

member.name: P:SsoCloud.SsoCloudRequest.Json
member.summary: If true, the login/logout result is returned as a JSON object

member.name: P:SsoCloud.SsoCloudRequest.Dest
member.summary: redirect to: "vault", "console", or "app.fooo", where the user is redirected to fooo:// (used for mobile)

member.name: P:SsoCloud.SsoCloudRequest.IdpSessionId
member.summary: If this value was provided in an SSO login response, send it when performing a logut request. Otherwise unused.

member.name: P:SsoCloud.SsoCloudRequest.ForceLogin
member.summary: On login, whether the user should be forced to re-enter their password even if they have an active session.

member.name: P:SsoCloud.SsoCloudRequest.Username
member.summary: Only used on Logout at this time.

member.name: T:SsoCloud.SsoCloudResponse
member.summary: * For security, this structure is used to return values from a Cloud SSO login or logout. It is encrypted with the key sent along with the SsoCloudRequest.

member.name: P:SsoCloud.SsoCloudResponse.MessageSessionUid
member.summary: If available, 16 bytes. Can not be zeros.

member.name: P:SsoCloud.SsoCloudResponse.EncryptedLoginToken
member.summary: Login only. Returned from a successful login. Send this to start_login.

member.name: P:SsoCloud.SsoCloudResponse.ProviderName
member.summary: The "domain name" associated with this user.

member.name: P:SsoCloud.SsoCloudResponse.IdpSessionId
member.summary: Some IdPs associate a sessionId with the session. If present, remember this and send it in the SsoCloudRequest when you logout.

member.name: P:SsoCloud.SsoCloudResponse.ErrorToken
member.summary: If there is an error this is a stringified JSON object. The "userInstructions" and "errorMessage" fields can be shown to the user.
